.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-8-2::.
6 different games are played: poker, bridge, monopoly, chess, scrabble, backgammon
The people use 6 different means of transport: ship, taxi, subway, tram, bike, snowmobile
 1. the person playing chess is not the person driving the snowmobile##6
 2. the person driving the snowmobile is in an even position##4
 3. the person driving the bike is not to the right of the person driving the tram##8
 4. the person playing monopoly is on the far left or far right##3
 5. the person driving the snowmobile is between the person playing chess and the person driving the taxi##2
 6. the person driving the ship is somewhere to the right of the person driving the subway##5
 7. the person driving the tram is somewhere to the right of the person playing monopoly##5
 8. the person driving the bike is on the left or right of the person driving the snowmobile##3
 9. the person playing bridge is not the person driving the tram##6
10. the person playing poker is on the far left or far right##3
11. the person playing scrabble is not to the left of the person driving the subway##8
12. the person driving the snowmobile is not to the right of the person playing scrabble##8
13. the person driving the bike is on the left or right of the person playing poker##3
14. the person playing backgammon is on the left of the person driving the taxi##1
15. the person driving the subway is somewhere to the left of the person playing chess##5

.:: Answer ::.
|         |      1      |      2      |      3       |   4    |    5    |    6    |
| Game   | monopoly | backgammon | bridge | scrabble | chess | poker |
| Transport     | subway  | ship  | taxi         | snowmobile | bike    | tram   |

